ad-rail-passenger-services-to-begin-on-june-30/articleshow/131929322.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-23T13:03:12+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131929371,imgsize-54999.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[US-Iran MoU outlines $300 billion Iran reconstruction fund — but who will pay the bill?]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131926566.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[US secretary of state Marco Rubio is heading to the Gulf amid controversy over a proposed $300 billion reconstruction fund for Iran. While critics decry it as a US payout, the administration claims Gulf states and private investors would largely finance it. However, some Arab allies fear a wealthier Iran could boost its regional influence and military might, sparking unease despite suggestions of significant foreign interest in investing.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/us-iran-mou-outlines-300-billion-iran-reconstruction-fund-but-who-will-pay-the-bill/articleshow/131926566.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/us-iran-mou-outlines-300-billion-iran-reconstruction-fund-but-who-will-pay-the-bill/articleshow/131926566.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-23T12:33:46+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131928245,imgsize-1171232.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Australian magician Daniel Hidden disappears without a trace after leaving a cryptic message, police launch massive search]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131927959.cms" /&