policies on energy, immigration, and foreign relations, suggesting they contributed to his downfall. Trump specifically pointed to Starmer's approach to North Sea oil and the UK's energy independence. He also mentioned a disagreement over the use of a British military base in Cyprus for US strikes on Iran, which he believes "hurt him badly."]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/he-hurt-himself-very-very-badly-trumps-blunt-response-to-keir-starmers-resignation-as-uk-pm/articleshow/131924591.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/he-hurt-himself-very-very-badly-trumps-blunt-response-to-keir-starmers-resignation-as-uk-pm/articleshow/131924591.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-23T11:18:03+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131924888,imgsize-950097.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Did Iran agree to IAEA inspections for 'nuclear honesty'? Trump, Vance say so]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131923088.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[The recent US-Iran nuclear discussions in Switzerland ended with mixed messages regarding inspection agreements. US Vice President Vance asserted that Iran had consented to IAEA inspector access, labeling it as a significant achievement. In contrast, Iran's Foreign Ministry spokesperson refuted any new commitments on nuclear matters, indicating that discussions had yet to begin. This discrepancy underscores the continuing frictions surrounding Tehran's nuclear program, particularly as Iran has previously curtailed IAEA access.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/did-iran-agree-to-iaea-inspections-for-nuclear-honesty-trump-vance-say-so/articleshow/131923088.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[http