at gnaws into the young coconut, the bat drinks the water]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131919741.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/south-asia/maldivian-wisdom-of-the-day-on-exploitation-injustice-the-rat-gnaws-into-the-young-coconut-the-bat-drinks-the-water/articleshow/131919741.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/south-asia/maldivian-wisdom-of-the-day-on-exploitation-injustice-the-rat-gnaws-into-the-young-coconut-the-bat-drinks-the-water/articleshow/131919741.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-23T00:49:03+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131919840,imgsize-250834.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Spanish proverb of the day: 'Tell me who you walk with, and I’ll tell you who you are']]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131918406.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/spanish-proverb-of-the-day-tell-me-who-you-walk-with-and-ill-tell-you-who-you-are-our-companions-shape-how-we-think-act-and-are-seen-by-the-world/articleshow/131918406.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/spanish-proverb-of-the-day-tell-me-who-you-walk-with-and-ill-tell-you-who-you-are-our-companions-shape-how-we-think-act-and-are-seen-by-the-world/articleshow/131918406.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-23T00:20:37+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131918762,imgsize-88574.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Portuguese proverb of the day: 'A thief who robs a thief has a hundred years of pardon']]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131918166.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A time-honored Portuguese saying, "Ladrão que rouba ladrão tem cem anos de perdão," translates to, "A thief who robs a thief has a hundred years of pardon." This adage embodies a universal tendency to relish when wrongdoers receive their due, suggesting a form of poetic justice. While it doesn’t legally validate such actions, it serves as a humorous nod to the complexities of morality and retribution in our justice systems.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/portuguese-proverb-of-the-day-a-thief-who-robs-a-thief-has-a-hundred-years-of-pardon-and-the-surprising-logic-behind-it/articleshow/131918166.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/portuguese-proverb-of-the-day-a-thief-who-robs-a-thief-has-a-hundred-years-of-pardon-and-the-surprising-logic-behind-it/articleshow/131918166.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-23T00:00:59+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131918373,imgsize-58894.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Malay proverb of the day on humility and resilience: Follow the nature of the rice plant; the more grains it bears, the lower it bows]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131918152.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/south-asia/malay-proverb-of-the-day-on-humility-and-resilience-follow-the-nature-of-the-rice-plant-the-more-grains-it-bears-the-lower-it-bows/articleshow/131918152.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesof